  <md:title>What Is Libertarianism?</md:title>
  <md:abstract>According to Dr. Stephen Davies, libertarianism is first and foremost a political doctrine.  Libertarians seek a society most conducive to human flourishing amongst autonomous self-defined individuals.  
Libertarians argue that this state of affairs is accomplished when the role of government and power is kept to a minimum. Although some have argued that libertarianism is a cult or rigid creed, Dr. Davies argues it is not, as there is a great deal of debate within the libertarian tradition.  These internal debates are a sign of intellectual vitality, and are healthy for any intellectual tradition.</md:abstract>
